---
import { Image, getImage } from "astro:assets";
import portraitDark from "../../../assets/about/portrait-dark.jpg";
import portraitLight from "../../../assets/about/portrait-light.webp";
import PageShell from "../components/PageShell.astro";
import SiteNav from "../components/SiteNav.astro";
import type { AboutKind } from "../types";

interface Props {
  kinds: AboutKind[];
}

const { kinds } = Astro.props;
const portraitWidths = [512, 768, 1024, 1536, 2048];
const portraitSizes = "(min-width: 768px) 50vw, 100vw";
const [portraitDarkAvif, portraitDarkWebp, portraitLightAvif, portraitLightWebp] =
  await Promise.all([
    getImage({ src: portraitDark, format: "avif", widths: portraitWidths, sizes: portraitSizes, quality: 82 }),
    getImage({ src: portraitDark, format: "webp", widths: portraitWidths, sizes: portraitSizes, quality: 82 }),
    getImage({ src: portraitLight, format: "avif", widths: portraitWidths, sizes: portraitSizes, quality: 82 }),
    getImage({ src: portraitLight, format: "webp", widths: portraitWidths, sizes: portraitSizes, quality: 82 }),
  ]);
---

<PageShell>
  <SiteNav revealBadge={false} />

  <article
    class="flex w-full flex-col gap-16 px-2 pt-2 pb-24 text-sm leading-[var(--tl-type-line-body)] text-[color:var(--tl-ink)] md:ml-auto md:w-1/2 md:pb-32 [&_a:hover]:opacity-70 [&_a]:text-inherit [&_a]:no-underline [&_h1]:m-0 [&_h2]:m-0 [&_h2]:max-w-[18ch] [&_h2]:text-inherit [&_h2]:leading-inherit [&_h2]:font-[var(--tl-type-heading-weight-strong)] [&_h2]:tracking-[0] [&_p]:m-0 [&_ul]:m-0 [&_ul]:list-none [&_ul]:p-0"
  >
    <figure class="m-0 w-full" aria-label="Portrait">
      <picture>
        <source
          media="(prefers-color-scheme: dark)"
          type="image/avif"
          srcset={portraitDarkAvif.srcSet.attribute}
          sizes={portraitSizes}
        />
        <source
          media="(prefers-color-scheme: dark)"
          type="image/webp"
          srcset={portraitDarkWebp.srcSet.attribute}
          sizes={portraitSizes}
        />
        <source
          media="(prefers-color-scheme: light)"
          type="image/avif"
          srcset={portraitLightAvif.srcSet.attribute}
          sizes={portraitSizes}
        />
        <source
          media="(prefers-color-scheme: light)"
          type="image/webp"
          srcset={portraitLightWebp.srcSet.attribute}
          sizes={portraitSizes}
        />
        <Image
          src={portraitLight}
          alt="Tom smiling in warm side light."
          widths={portraitWidths}
          sizes={portraitSizes}
          quality={82}
          priority
          class="h-auto w-full"
        />
      </picture>
    </figure>

    <header class="flex max-w-xs flex-col gap-3 md:fixed md:top-1/2 md:left-2 md:w-[calc(50%-1rem)] md:-translate-y-1/2">
      <h1
        class="text-[var(--tl-type-display-md)] leading-[var(--tl-type-line-tight)] font-[var(--tl-type-heading-weight-strong)] tracking-[0] md:text-inherit md:leading-inherit md:font-inherit"
      >
        About
      </h1>
      <p class="md:max-w-xs md:opacity-60">
        I'm Tom Schönmann. thinkinglabs is my public working surface: a markdown repository
        turned into a website, feed system, index, and agent-readable map of my work.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="flex max-w-xs flex-col gap-4" aria-labelledby="about-what-title">
      <h2 id="about-what-title">A desk left in public</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 opacity-70">
        <p>
          It is not a portfolio and not quite a blog. It holds rough thoughts, stricter claims,
          predictions, project notes, decisions, questions, and the outside inputs that changed
          the shape of the work.
        </p>
        <p>
          I work mostly on AI systems and the operational layer around them. The parts I care
          about tend to be the parts that make systems legible: what changed, why a decision was
          made, what evidence supports a claim, and what would make me change my mind.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="flex max-w-xs flex-col gap-4" aria-labelledby="about-system-title">
      <h2 id="about-system-title">The repository is the durable object</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 opacity-70">
        <p>
          The web UI, JSON feeds, SQLite index, MCP surfaces, and Markdown URL variants are
          derived views over the same source. {
            "Canonical public content pages, listings, and selected static pages"
          } have agent-readable Markdown siblings by appending
          <code>.md</code> to the slashless URL, with <code>/index.md</code> standing in for the
          homepage.
        </p>
        <p>
          That keeps the machine surface rigid without making the writing brittle: edit the
          files, rebuild the surfaces, and let the public version stay close to the working
          version.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="flex max-w-xs flex-col gap-6" aria-labelledby="about-inventory-title">
      <header class="flex flex-col gap-4">
        <h2 id="about-inventory-title">The public shape of the repository</h2>
        <p class="opacity-70">
          Each entry type has a job. Some are loose enough to catch a thought before it
          disappears; others are strict enough to make drift visible.
        </p>
      </header>

      <ul class="flex flex-col gap-1">
        {
          kinds.map((kind) => (
            <li>
              <a class="text-sm leading-[var(--tl-type-line-body)]" href={kind.href} aria-label={`${kind.name}: ${kind.gloss}`}>
                {kind.name}
              </a>
            </li>
          ))
        }
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="flex max-w-xs flex-col gap-4" aria-labelledby="about-reading-title">
      <h2 id="about-reading-title">Incomplete is part of the contract</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 opacity-70">
        <p>
          A claim can be revised. A prediction can resolve badly. A project can go dormant. The
          useful thing is not that every object is polished, but that the system leaves enough
          structure behind to return later and inspect what happened.
        </p>
        <p>
          I want the tone of the site to stay calm because the work benefits from calm. There
          should be enough empty space to read a sentence, enough metadata to audit it, and not
          much more than that.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="flex max-w-xs flex-col gap-4" aria-labelledby="about-work-title">
      <h2 id="about-work-title">AI systems, made legible</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 opacity-70">
        <p>
          I work for <a href="https://wild.as">wild.as</a>. Reach out at
          <a href="mailto:tom@wild.as">tom@wild.as</a> or
          <a href="mailto:tom@flaming.codes">tom@flaming.codes</a> for personal messages.
          My other main site is <a href="https://flaming.codes">flaming.codes</a>, which I used
          in the past for traditional blogging and knowledge sharing.
        </p>
        <p>
          Wild works with new technologies in the pragmatic sense: putting new capabilities into
          production when they make software clearer, faster, or more useful. A large part of that
          work right now is agentic software engineering: using agents every day, building the
          harnesses around them, and learning where human judgment still has to stay close to the
          loop.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <footer class="max-w-xs opacity-60">
      Built with Astro, markdown content collections, deterministic feeds, a derived SQLite
      index, and a small MCP server for agent access. The typography and navigation are meant to
      make the repository feel like a working surface rather than a publication schedule.
    </footer>
  </article>
</PageShell>
